# Copy this file to admin/.env.local and fill in real values.
# admin/.env.local is gitignored — never commit it.
#
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL is the same project URL used by the main app's .env.local.
#
# VITE_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY is the Supabase "service_role" key (Project Settings > API >
# Project API keys > service_role), NOT the anon key. It bypasses Row Level Security entirely,
# which is what lets this local-only tool read every player's runs. Never put this key in the
# main app's .env.local or in any file under src/ — it must only ever be referenced from admin/,
# which is never built or deployed (see admin/vite.config.ts).

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# Optional — enables the "Insights" tab (Claude-powered run analysis + follow-up Q&A).
# Get a key at console.anthropic.com. Calls go straight from this local admin app to the
# Anthropic API using your own key, so usage is billed to your Anthropic account. Leave unset
# to skip this feature entirely — the rest of the admin tool works fine without it.
VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-anthropic-api-key
# Optional override; defaults to claude-sonnet-5 if unset.
# VITE_ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-5

# Optional — adds an "Analyze with Local LLM" button next to Claude in Insights. Runs entirely on
# your own machine via Ollama (https://ollama.com): free, private, no API key. Needs no env vars
# to work with Ollama's defaults — only set these if you're running Ollama on a different
# host/port or want a different model than llama3.1. See admin/src/lib/ollamaClient.ts for setup
# notes (installing Ollama, pulling a model, and opening CORS for this dev server's origin).
# VITE_OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434
# Defaults to llama3.2:3b (~2GB) rather than a bigger model — on a laptop where other apps already
# claim most of your RAM, a bigger model can push the whole system into swap, which looks like a
# hang (fans maxed, no output for minutes) but is really just disk thrashing. If `ollama ps` shows
# your model at 100% CPU and Activity Monitor shows heavy swap use, that's this — try a smaller
# model or free up RAM rather than assuming local analysis just doesn't work on your machine.
# VITE_OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.2:3b
# Context window size in tokens, passed as num_ctx. Defaults to 4096, paired with a much smaller
# run-data prompt than Claude gets (see RunInsights.tsx) so it reliably fits with headroom to
# spare. Lower this further if still thrashing; raise it only if you've confirmed you have RAM to
# spare (check Activity Monitor's memory pressure / swap while a request is running).
# VITE_OLLAMA_NUM_CTX=4096
